Convolvulus pilosellifolius var. linearifolius 
<normalizedToken id="1D08457871DFC2D835DD54791699FE4D" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
, Meded. Bot. Mus. Herb. Rijks Univ. Utrecht 281: 191. 1967. (
<normalizedToken id="6BBC6EE428F1FCFAAB05BE66112C354A" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967: 191).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AFF9FAD015EC753F018ED5162164138" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="type">
<paragraph id="95A6A205844865254056FFD9BCF9DA70" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC1134DFAF8BEB6859F785EF420B6608" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
IRAN, Bushehr, 
<emphasis id="761DB93A9D9D421A60E6EF0158B45468" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Koie</emphasis>
268 (holotype B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="55C9A02C9310C05DEB60016A333B5A72" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="9AEE35885133DEB3604F65D403A32CBB" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DAE952FE7B9BA7912CB53F437F633839" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">This is a delicate form with linear-lanceolate leaves to 2 cm wide and mostly solitary flowers.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72742AEDAF192FBCE76269B576A39D4E" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2C02397E76D970F552958C8775E69776" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2176F1CC62B0DAE4CB55E907A32CC909" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
The occasional specimen of this variety occurs throughout most of the range of 
<taxonomicName id="21A631C19BC807C5EC88BB1FD461E47D" authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pilosellifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosellifolius">
<emphasis id="540BEC291FE1CF451E99B0DA4A0F97D5" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus pilosellifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but especially around the Arabian/Persian Gulf, such as 
<emphasis id="5FAB12577DD697D3A5F7865D63BC9375" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Good</emphasis>
193 from Bahrain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FE64ECFB34A35D23890B0045E5D829F8" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="notes">
<paragraph id="78F44CEDE7E355441224E0CE5C06320D" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32818200D450BC3D56A6803EE5CF393D" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicName id="CE7E25B7DD8A3CA47C0193D9A1B61D0C" authorityName="Desr., Encycl. [Lamarck et al.] 3: 551. 1792. (Desrousseaux" authorityYear="1792" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus pilosellifolius" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilosellifolius">
<emphasis id="70E89FFBC751B94D40871CA2FE402E79" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus pilosellifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="AC58C06FE102228D196FCE6B0F439191" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 158. 1753. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus cantabrica" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cantabrica">
<emphasis id="7B006A4D6404F2DDA9B74E9637459101" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus cantabrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially forms of that species previously assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="B158BB87CCF7C53BE9E2238E6D4F1A1D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus linearis" order="Solanales" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="C7816094C003C427A200FF2B0CE2BCE9" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Convolvulus linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the shorter corolla (to 15 mm) and glabrous ovary and capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
